BkCinasw9.content:
# Detection of LPP buffer overload.

* A low power payload (LPP) is created with a size of 4 bytes.

* Firing tweak-pulse **A** empties the LPP before adding a voltage measurement. A voltage measurement occupies 4 bytes, so fits inside the LPP buffer.

* Firing tweak-pulse **B** empties the LPP, then attempts to add a GPS measurement. This GPS measurement occupies 11 bytes and do can't fit inside the LPP buffer. The get-error node reports an "overflow" error.

@/02-example.description: Patch to show how overflow of the payload buffer can be detected using the get-error node. Run in debugger.

description: Cayenne Low Power Payload with Extended Data Types. CayenneLPP format is an efficient way to send sensor data over low bit rate connection, like LoRa. Wraps https://github.com/ElectronicCats/CayenneLPP.
